50|$|The {{distance}} {{over which}} radio communications is useful depends significantly on {{things other than}} wavelength, such as transmitter power, receiver quality, type, size, and height of antenna, mode of transmission, noise, and interfering <b>signals.</b> <b>Ground</b> waves, tropospheric scatter and skywaves can all achieve greater ranges than line-of-sight propagation. The study of radio propagation allows estimates of useful range to be made.|$|R
