2500|$|In December 1942, the War Department {{directed}} the Signal Corps General Development Laboratories and the Camp Evans Signal Lab to combine into the <b>Signal</b> Corps <b>Ground</b> Service (SCGS) with headquarters at Bradley Beach, New Jersey (Hotel Grossman). The Department also {{directed the}} <b>Signal</b> Corps <b>Ground</b> Service to cut total {{military and civilian}} personnel from 14,518 military and civilian personnel to 8,879 by August 1943. In June 1944, [...] "Signees", former Italian prisoners of war, arrived at Fort Monmouth to perform housekeeping duties. A lieutenant colonel and 500 enlisted men became hospital, mess, and repair shop attendants, relieving American soldiers from these duties.|$|R
